), rough dorsal skin with tubercles (vs. smooth dorsal skin in 

G. megdogensis

), and brown to beige background color of dorsal surface of head, body and limbs in life (vs. green in 

G. megdogensis

); from 

G. carinensis

by the relatively smaller body size in females, SVL 
34.9–35.4 mm
(vs. 
38 mm
in 

G. carinensis

), more developed webbing (webbing formula of the fourth toe (3) IV (3)) (vs. webbing formula (2½) IV (2) in 

G. carinensis

